semantic_equivalence_artifact.original_latex_theorem:
\label{prop:log etale dimensions}
Let $f:X\rightarrow Y$ be a morphism of fs log stacks.
\begin{enumerate}
\item If $f$ is log \'etale, then $f$ has log fibre dimension $0$.
\item If $f$ is integral, log \'etale and $Y$ pure-dimensional,
then $\dim X=\dim Y$.
\item If $X$ and $Y$ carry coherent idealized structures and
$f$ is integral and idealized log \'etale (but not necessarily log
\'etale), then $\dim X \le \dim Y$.
\end{enumerate}

